          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-3-1689773651336-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has begun to soften, add your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>cornflour</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong>, the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>orange[s] </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>carnitas sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1689773654461-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1689773654461-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1689773654461-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1689773654461-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1689773654461-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the carnitas sauce with your <strong>duck leg[s] </strong>(along with the jelly and fat!), skin-side up, and put the dish in the oven, uncovered for 30 min</p><p>After 30 min, remove the dish from the oven, and shred the <strong>duck meat</strong> off the bone, then discard the bone</p><p>Mix it all together – this is your <strong>duck carnitas</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-3-1689773660446-x200.jpg",
